						"boxes" : [ 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"id" : "obj-2",
									"linecount" : 39,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 416.518511950969696, 6.962963163852692, 389.0, 529.0 ],
									"text" : "TO THE SKETCH: GUI\n\nactivedotcolor - sets dot (the dot is signaling, that the step is an onset part of imported or generated sequence) color for active steps\n\nsyntax:\n    activedotcolor red green blue\n    (red, green, blue: 0-255)\n\nbgcolor - sets background color (visible only if opaque mode is used)\n\nsyntax:\n    bgcolor red green blue\n    (red, green, blue: 0-255)\n\nhighlightcolor - sets highlight color\n\nsyntax:\n    highlightcolor red green blue\n    (red, green, blue: 0-255)\n\ninactivedotcolor - sets dot (the dot is signaling, that the step is an onset part of imported or generated sequence) color for inactive steps\n\nsyntax:\n    inactivedotcolor red green blue\n    (red, green, blue: 0-255)\n\nopaque - sets opaque/transparent mode\n\nsyntax:\n    opaque mode\n    (mode: 0 - transparent, 1 - opaque)\n\ntilecolor - sets tile color\n\nsyntax:\n    tilecolor red green blue\n    (red, green, blue: 0-255)"
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"id" : "obj-1",
									"linecount" : 45,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 12.814814984798431, 6.962963163852692, 387.0, 623.0 ],
									"text" : "TO THE SKETCH: HANDLING SEQUENCES\n\neucl - generates Euclidean rhythmic pattern\n\nsyntax:\n    eucl trackIndex numberOfSteps numberOfTriggers offset\n    (trackIndex is 0-based)\n\ngetpattern - querying the statuses of all steps in a track (see also \"pattern\" in FROM THE SKETCH).\n\nsyntax:\n    getpattern trackIndex\n    (trackIndex is 0-based, mesage with no trackIndex or if trackIndex <\n    0 all patterns will be broadcasted)\n\nhighlight - sets highlighted step within indicated track\n\nsyntax:\n    highlight trackIndex stepIndex\n    (trackIndex and stepIndex are 0-based; use negative stepIndex to \n    deselect step within indicated track)\n\nhusk - querying the status of a single step in a track (see also \"husk\" in FROM THE SKETCH). Note: do not use this message for event-precision sequencing (for this kind of applications you have to build a structure based on Max native objects - as this entire example shows)\n\nsyntax:\n    husk trackIndex stepIndex\n    (trackIndex and stepIndex are 0-based)\n\ninit - clears all sequence data and sets the number of sequencer tracks\n\nsyntax:\n    init numberOfTracks\n\nsetpattern - sets arbitrary rhythmic pattern on the indicated track\n\nsyntax:\n    setpattern trackIndex binarySequence\n    (trackIndex is 0-based, binarySequence is a symbol composed from\n    zeros and ones, representing the pattern, e.g. 1010 is a 4-step\n    pattern with onsets at first and third step)\n"
								}

							}
, 							{
								"box" : 								{
									"id" : "obj-7",
									"linecount" : 42,
									"maxclass" : "comment",
									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 822.592586040496826, 6.962963163852692, 391.0, 570.0 ],
									"text" : "FROM THE SKETCH\n\nThe messages generated by the sketch used in this example are marked with prefixes enclosed by [ ] (brackets).\n\n[console] - notifications, error messages, etc.\n\nsyntax:\n    [console] message\n    (list [the prefix and the message])\n\n[init_complete] - notification sent when you change configuration (number of tracks) of sequencer via \"init\" message\n\nsyntax:\n    [init_complete] numberOfTracks\n    (list [the prefix and numberOfTracks])\n\n[husk] - prefix for data achived via \"husk\" message sent to the sketch  this message is sent when you change configuration (number of tracks) of sequencer via \"init\" message\n\nsyntax:\n    [husk] trackIndex stepIndex stepStatus\n    (list, trackIndex and stepIndex are 0-based, stepStatus is 0 or 1; \n    expect -1 value of trackIndex, stepIndex or stepStatus when NaN on \n    incorrect values are provided with the message sent to the sketch)\n\n[pattern] - a message containing binary sequence representing single track prepended by track index (0-based). This message is generated when you alter pattern manually or it can be forced by the \"getpattern\" message sent to the sketch\n\nsyntax:\n    [pattern] trackIndex stepStatus_1 stepStatus_2 ... stepStatus_n\n    (list, trackIndex is 0-based, stepStatus_x is 0 or 1)\n\n[setup_complete] - prefix for the message sent when setup function (in p5js JavaScript code) is completed\n\nsyntax:\n    [setup_complete]"
								}

							}
 ],
