									"numinlets" : 1,
									"numoutlets" : 0,
									"patching_rect" : [ 539.0, 33.0, 464.0, 141.0 ],
									"text" : "This subpatch features a bank of 4 simple, but fully functional drum sequencers built around [coll] object. For the sake of precision, it's best to build sequencers based on native Max objects (because [jweb] works in a seperate asynchronous process, and you can't rely on having sent and outputted messages within the same event. Of course, you can build any other sequencing constructs you want - Max provides many objectsa, mechanisms, approaches to facilitate this task.\n\nSo, native Max objects \"capture\" all the data transmitted by [jweb] - technically there is some redundancy to it, but this solution is very practical, it allows both easy editing of patterns as well as their precise sequencing."
								}

